## 3. Core Modules

The platform is split into twelve Django apps. Each app owns its own models, serializers, views, and permissions. This keeps the codebase modular and makes it possible to assign modules to different developers or sprints independently.

| Module | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `accounts` | Authentication, JWT issuance/refresh, password reset, 2FA, role assignment. |
| `researchers` | Researcher profile, skill tags, reputation score, badges. |
| `companies` | Company profile, verification, team members, analytics dashboard. |
| `programs` | Program creation/approval, scope (in/out), rules, safe harbor, reward table. |
| `reports` | Vulnerability report submission, status machine, comments, attachments. |
| `triage` | Triage queue, severity adjustment, duplicate detection, bounty recommendation. |
| `rewards` | Reward wallet, approval workflow, payout integration (bKash/Nagad/SSLCommerz). |
| `notifications` | Email + in-app notifications for status changes and comments. |
| `leaderboard` | Aggregated researcher rankings, monthly/all-time views. |
| `auditlogs` | Immutable log of admin, company, and triage actions. |
| `adminpanel` | Platform-wide admin operations: users, companies, programs, disputes. |
| `cms` | Static/marketing pages, policy pages, help center content. |

