## 4. Roles & Permissions

### 4.1 Role Definitions

| Role | Description |
|---|---|
| `researcher` | Independent security researcher who browses programs and submits reports. |
| `company_admin` | Owner-level user for a registered company; manages program and team. |
| `company_member` | Company team member assigned to specific reports by `company_admin`. |
| `triage_analyst` | Platform-side analyst who validates and scores incoming reports. |
| `platform_admin` | Full administrative access across the platform. |

### 4.2 Permission Matrix

Simplified matrix below. The actual implementation should use DRF permission classes combined with object-level checks (e.g., django-guardian or custom `has_object_permission` logic), never relying on frontend checks alone.

| Action | Researcher | Company | Triage | Admin |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| View public programs | Yes | Own only | Yes | Yes |
| Submit report | Yes | No | No | No |
| View own reports | Yes | N/A | Yes | Yes |
| View reports on own program | No | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| Change report status | No | Limited | Yes | Yes |
| Approve reward | No | Yes | Recommend | Yes |
| Approve program | No | Submit only | No | Yes |
| Approve company | No | No | No | Yes |
| View audit logs | No | No | No | Yes |

> **Security Note:** Role checks must always be enforced server-side at the object level. A researcher must never be able to fetch a report by ID outside their own ownership, and a company must never be able to fetch a report outside its own program, even if they guess a valid UUID.

