## 5. Data Model

The schema below is the recommended baseline for the MVP and is designed to extend cleanly into the post-MVP feature set (private programs, CVSS scoring, SLA tracking) without breaking migrations.

### 5.1 Entity Relationship Overview

```text
User ──1:1── ResearcherProfile
User ──1:1── CompanyProfile (for company_admin owner)
CompanyProfile ──1:N── CompanyTeamMember ──N:1── User
CompanyProfile ──1:N── Program
Program ──1:N── ScopeAsset (in_scope / out_of_scope)
Program ──1:N── RewardTier
Program ──1:N── VulnerabilityReport
ResearcherProfile ──1:N── VulnerabilityReport
VulnerabilityReport ──1:N── ReportComment
VulnerabilityReport ──1:N── ReportAttachment
VulnerabilityReport ──1:N── ReportStatusHistory
VulnerabilityReport ──1:1── Reward (nullable)
VulnerabilityReport ──N:1── TriageAnalyst (assigned_to, nullable)
User ──1:N── AuditLogEntry
```

### 5.2 Core Tables

#### 5.2.1 User (`accounts`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | Primary key for all user-facing IDs (avoid sequential IDs for security) |
| `email` | varchar(255), unique | Used as login identifier |
| `password_hash` | varchar(255) | Django's PBKDF2/Argon2 hasher |
| `role` | varchar(20) | `researcher` \| `company_admin` \| `company_member` \| `triage_analyst` \| `platform_admin` |
| `is_active` | boolean | Soft-disable without deleting |
| `is_2fa_enabled` | boolean | Required true for `company_admin` and `platform_admin` |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |
| `updated_at` | timestamp | |

#### 5.2.2 ResearcherProfile (`researchers`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `user_id` | UUID, FK → User | 1:1 |
| `display_name` | varchar(100) | |
| `bio` | text | Nullable |
| `skill_tags` | JSONB | Array of strings, e.g. `["web", "mobile", "api"]` |
| `reputation_score` | integer, default 0 | Derived from accepted reports and severity |
| `country` | varchar(100) | Nullable |
| `wallet_balance` | decimal(12,2), default 0 | Denormalized cache of approved + paid rewards |

#### 5.2.3 CompanyProfile (`companies`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `owner_user_id` | UUID, FK → User | `company_admin` |
| `company_name` | varchar(150) | |
| `website` | varchar(255) | |
| `verification_status` | varchar(20) | `pending` \| `verified` \| `rejected` |
| `verification_notes` | text | Internal, admin-only |
| `logo_url` | varchar(255) | Nullable |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |

#### 5.2.4 Program (`programs`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `company_id` | UUID, FK → CompanyProfile | |
| `title` | varchar(150) | |
| `program_type` | varchar(20) | `vdp` \| `bbp` |
| `visibility` | varchar(10) | `public` \| `private` (private is post-MVP) |
| `status` | varchar(20) | `draft` \| `pending_approval` \| `approved` \| `paused` \| `closed` |
| `description` | text | |
| `rules` | text | |
| `safe_harbor_policy` | text | Nullable |
| `created_at` / `updated_at` | timestamp | |

#### 5.2.5 ScopeAsset (`programs`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `program_id` | UUID, FK → Program | |
| `asset_type` | varchar(30) | `domain` \| `api` \| `mobile_app` \| `source_code` \| `other` |
| `asset_value` | varchar(255) | e.g. `*.example.com` |
| `scope` | varchar(15) | `in_scope` \| `out_of_scope` |
| `notes` | text | Nullable |

#### 5.2.6 RewardTier (`programs`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `program_id` | UUID, FK → Program | |
| `severity` | varchar(15) | `critical` \| `high` \| `medium` \| `low` \| `informational` |
| `min_amount` | decimal(12,2) | BDT |
| `max_amount` | decimal(12,2) | BDT |

#### 5.2.7 VulnerabilityReport (`reports`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `program_id` | UUID, FK → Program | |
| `researcher_id` | UUID, FK → ResearcherProfile | |
| `title` | varchar(200) | |
| `description` | text | |
| `steps_to_reproduce` | text | |
| `proof_of_concept` | text | Nullable; may reference attachment IDs |
| `affected_asset` | varchar(255) | |
| `severity` | varchar(15) | Set by researcher initially, adjustable by triage |
| `cvss_score` | decimal(3,1) | Nullable, post-MVP |
| `status` | varchar(25) | See Section 6.2 Report Status List |
| `assigned_triage_id` | UUID, FK → User | Nullable |
| `duplicate_of_id` | UUID, FK → VulnerabilityReport | Nullable, self-referential |
| `submitted_at` | timestamp | |
| `resolved_at` | timestamp | Nullable |
| `closed_at` | timestamp | Nullable |

#### 5.2.8 ReportStatusHistory (`reports`)

Append-only table; never updated, only inserted. This is the audit trail for the report lifecycle and is what powers SLA tracking in the post-MVP phase.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `report_id` | UUID, FK → VulnerabilityReport | |
| `from_status` | varchar(25) | Nullable for the first entry |
| `to_status` | varchar(25) | |
| `changed_by_id` | UUID, FK → User | |
| `note` | text | Nullable |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |

#### 5.2.9 ReportComment (`reports`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `report_id` | UUID, FK → VulnerabilityReport | |
| `author_id` | UUID, FK → User | |
| `body` | text | |
| `is_internal` | boolean, default false | `true` = triage/company-only note, hidden from researcher |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |

#### 5.2.10 ReportAttachment (`reports`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `report_id` | UUID, FK → VulnerabilityReport | |
| `uploaded_by_id` | UUID, FK → User | |
| `file_url` | varchar(500) | S3 object key/URL, never local disk path |
| `file_name` | varchar(255) | |
| `file_size_bytes` | integer | |
| `content_type` | varchar(100) | Validated against an allow-list |
| `scanned_status` | varchar(20) | `pending` \| `clean` \| `flagged` |

#### 5.2.11 Reward (`rewards`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `report_id` | UUID, FK → VulnerabilityReport | 1:1 |
| `amount` | decimal(12,2) | BDT |
| `status` | varchar(20) | `recommended` \| `approved` \| `processing` \| `paid` \| `rejected` |
| `payout_method` | varchar(20) | `bkash` \| `nagad` \| `sslcommerz` \| `bank_transfer` |
| `payout_reference` | varchar(100) | Nullable, external transaction ID |
| `approved_by_id` | UUID, FK → User | Nullable |
| `paid_at` | timestamp | Nullable |

#### 5.2.12 AuditLogEntry (`auditlogs`)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID, PK | |
| `actor_id` | UUID, FK → User | |
| `action` | varchar(100) | e.g. `program.approved`, `report.status_changed` |
| `target_type` | varchar(50) | Model name |
| `target_id` | UUID | |
| `metadata` | JSONB | Before/after values where relevant |
| `ip_address` | varchar(45) | |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |

> **Schema Notes**
> - All primary keys are UUIDs, not auto-increment integers, to prevent ID enumeration of reports and programs.
> - `ReportStatusHistory` and `AuditLogEntry` are append-only — never issue UPDATE or DELETE against these tables from application code.
> - `wallet_balance` on `ResearcherProfile` is a denormalized cache; the `Reward` table is the source of truth and should be recomputed/reconciled periodically.

